## ğŸ“˜ How to Use / Run the Project

1. Download or clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone `https://paballokoketso121-maker.github.io/Green-leaf-P3/`

  
Greenleaf Organic â€” Website
 What's included
- `index.html`, `about.html`, `faq.html`, `products.html`, `shop.html`, `services.html`, `contact.html`
- `css/style.css` â€” central styles
- `js/script.js` â€” interactive behaviors (hamburger, accordion, lightbox, search, contact)
- `send-email.php` â€” server-side contact form processor (simple mail())
- `images/` â€” image assets; use the filenames listed in the project structure

Deployment checklist
1. Upload files preserving the folder structure.
2. Edit `send-email.php`: replace `$to = 'paballokoketso121@gmail.com'` with your real recipient address.
3. Ensure your host supports PHP for the contact form (or replace with your mail API).
4. Replace `https://example.com` canonical/og links with your real domain in HTML head tags.
5. Replace the map placeholder in `contact.html` with a Google Maps iframe if needed.
6. For production email, use PHPMailer or SMTP (recommended), and add spam protection (CAPTCHA) and rate limiting.
7. Optimize images (serve WebP or responsive `srcset`) and enable HTTPS.
Notes & improvements
- The contact form uses `mail()` for demonstration. For reliable delivery use authenticated SMTP.
- Add `sitemap.xml` and `robots.txt` for SEO.
- Consider server-side validation and logging for contact attempts.
